ponents commodity trading minerals energy ranching glass and investments worldwide it produces transportation fuels petrochemicals ethanol asphalts base oils gasoline jet fuel diesel biodiesel and heating oils operates pipelines that transport crude oil refined petroleum products ethanol natural gas liquids and chemicals and manufactures building and consumer products tissue packaging paper cellulose and chemi koch industries inc through its subsidiaries engages in the business of refining chemicals biofuels and ingredients forest and consumer products fertilizers polymers and fibers process and pollution control equipment and technologies electronic components commodity trading minerals energy ranching glass and investments worldwide it produces transportation fuels petrochemicals ethanol asphalts base oils gasoline jet fuel diesel biodiesel and heating oils operates pipelines that transport crude oil refined petroleum products ethanol natural gas liquids and chemicals and manufactures building and consumer products tissue packaging paper cellulose and chemicals it produces chemical intermediates polymers and plastics fibers and fabrics and specialty chemicals manufactures antennas application tooling cable assemblies connected lighting connectors copper flex electrical products industrial automation membrane switches optical solutions and pcb assemblies for aerospace and defense automotive commercial vehicle connected lighting consumerhome appliance data and computing electricalindustrial medical industrial automation scientific smart phones and devices energy telecommunicationsnetworking and wireless infrastructure produces fertilizers and plant nutrients and produces methanol for use in daily products it markets trades and handles drybulk commodities engages in oil and gas exploration and production oil field products steel and more supplies and trades crude oil refined petroleum products natural gas industrial metals and other valued commodities and operates ranches for breeding commercial cattle for beef products and horses for marketing to select forums the company was formerly known as rock island oil  refining co inc and changed its name to koch industries inc in  the company was founded in  and is based in wichita kansas with subsidiaries in the united states detailed description  east th street northwichita ks united statesfounded in  phone  fax  wwwkochindcom key executives for koch industries inc mr charles g koch coowner chairman of the board and chief executive officer age  mr david l robertson president chief operating officer and director mr steven j feilmeier chief financial officer executive vice president and director age  mr james b hannan executive vice president and chief executive officer of enterprises age  mr bradley j razook executive vice president and chief executive officer of resources age  compensation as of fiscal year  koch industries inc key developments koch industries inc announces executive changes mar   koch industries inc has announced the promotion of key leaders to newly created positions within the company koch says in an emailed press release that jim hannan president and ceo of the companys georgiapacific unit has been named executive vice president and ceo of enterprises in addition brad razook president and ceo of kochs flint hills resources has been named executive vice president and ceo of resources in those new roles hannan will oversee koch companies georgiapacific invista molex and guardian as well as the recently acquired stake in business software and cloud computing company infor in other koch executive news the company said that martin slark ceo of molex has been elected to the koch industries board of directors the company also announced four appointments to the officer level at the company as follows david dotson  vice president operations and compliance philip ellender  vice president government and public affairs matt flamini  vice president business development walt 